obo:ECO_0006004  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_434  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Array Tomography, a tool for imaging the molecular architecture and ultrastructure of neuronal circuitry\n\n25/4/2017 Pim\n- Authors use SubSynMAP --> a novel combination of previously developed volumetric super-resolution imaging of deconvolution array tomography (ATD). This technique uses the computational integration of wide-field fluorescence images to derive super-resolution level data on intracellular localization.\n- The authors state \"The application of our synapse analysis method demonstrates that, across synapse classes and cortical layers, FXR1P and FXR2P unlike FMRP are preferentially localized to the post-synaptic region (Figure 7A-D, Figure 7-figure supplement 1A-D); but like FMRP, the distributions of FXR1P and FXR2P peak away from the synaptic cleft\".\nThis data justifies annotation against \"postsynapse\".\n\n10/05/2017 Tilmann\n- The authors state on page 11: \"FXR2P unlike FMRP are preferentially localized\nto the post-synaptic region (Figure 7A-D, Figure 7-figure supplement 1A-D)\". Experimental description: Cortical mouse brain were analysed. Concerning strain and age of the animals, the Material and Methods refer to a paper Micheva and Smith 2007 (Neuron) but no information there is on the age or strain." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_434" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

